 years of postwar Japan through the lens of history. The contributors to this book seek to offer such a view. As they examine three related themes of postwar history, the authors describe an ongoing historical process marked by unexpected changes, such as Japan's extraordinary economic growth, and unanticipated continuities, such as the endurance of conservative rule. A provocative set of interpretative essays by eminent scholars, this book will appeal to anyone interested in the history of twentieth-century Japan and the dilemmas facing Japan today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a21st century.  aacademic.  aasian countries.  aasian history.  acontemporary.  aeastern world.  aeconomic power.  aeconomics.  aeconomy.  aessay collection.  ainternational.  ajapan.  ajapanese economy.  ajapanese government.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese politics.  ajapanese power.  ajapanese.  amodern history.  amodern world.  apostwar japan.  apostwar.  aresearch.  ascholarly.  asocial problems.  asocial science.  asocial scientists.  awartime.  aworld history.  aworld war 2.  awwii.1 aAndrew, Gordon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruce, Cumings, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarol, Gluck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharles Yuji, Horioka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank K., Upham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGary D., Allinson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJ. Victor, Koschmann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re